<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="491" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bispo &amp; Froehlich" authorityYear="2004" box="[321,585,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandaoi">
<emphasis box="[321,585,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">Anacroneuria brandaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described at the Serra da Mesa, in the north of 
<collectingRegion box="[1205,1327,367,393]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
(Bispo &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich, C. G." box="[151,326,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref8880" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2004) Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Boraceia Biological Station, Sao Paulo, Brazil. Aquatic Insects, 26 (1), 55 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.1076 / aqin. 26.1.53.35377" type="journal article" year="2004">Froehlich 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In this work, we recorded the species in the Chapada dos Veadeiros and Serra dos Pireneus, 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. The penial armature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bispo &amp; Froehlich" authorityYear="2004" box="[487,623,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandaoi">
<emphasis box="[487,623,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">A. brandaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of the 
<typeStatus box="[902,1000,439,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zwick 1972)" baseAuthorityName="Zwick" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[1041,1315,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[1041,1149,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">A. debilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[1164,1307,439,465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" pagination="1123 - 1194" refId="ref10509" refString="Zwick, P. (1972) Die Plecopteren Pictets und Burmeisters, mit Angaben uber weitere Arten (Insecta). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 78, 1123 - 1194. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 97087" type="journal article" year="1972">Zwick 1972</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, recent studies of different populations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zwick" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[616,722,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[616,722,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">A. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baldin, C. &amp; Bispo P. C. &amp; Novaes, M. C." box="[737,944,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" pagination="391 - 397" refId="ref8021" refString="Baldin, C., Bispo P. C. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2013) New species and records of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 3694 (4), 391 - 397. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.4.7" type="journal article" year="2013">
Baldin 
<emphasis box="[821,871,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bispo, P. C. &amp; Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C." box="[956,1153,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" pagination="591 - 596" refId="ref8412" refString="Bispo, P. C., Costa, L. S. M. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2014) Two new species and a new record of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Central Brazil. Zootaxa, 3779 (5), 591 - 596. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3779.5.9" type="journal article" year="2014">
Bispo 
<emphasis box="[1029,1079,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[1165,1428,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" pagination="458 - 468" refId="ref9553" refString="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2014 a) A new species and notes on Perlidae (Plecoptera) from Parana and Santa Catarina States, southern Brazil. Zootaxa, 3765 (5), 458 - 468. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3765.5.4" type="journal article" year="2014">Novaes &amp; Bispo 2014a</bibRefCitation>
) revealed high variability in the penial armature, which could overlap with that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bispo &amp; Froehlich" authorityYear="2004" box="[1069,1190,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandoi">
<emphasis box="[1069,1190,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">A. brandoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Herein, we observed that the penial armature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bispo &amp; Froehlich" authorityYear="2004" box="[454,588,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandaoi">
<emphasis box="[454,588,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">A. brandaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more rounded keel and that the apex tapers less abruptly (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1372,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1816,1840]" captionTargetBox="[169,1422,643,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-241@4.[151,1435,633,1793]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Comparison between adults of Anacroneuria brandaoi from Rio das Almas (A–D) and from Córrego Vagafogo (E–H). A, E: head and pronotum; B, F: penial armatures in lateral view; C, G: same, dorsal view; D, H: ventral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816763" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816763/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) than that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zwick" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[230,337,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[230,337,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="491">A. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same location.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
